'''Lwandle''' is a township in [[Somerset West]]a town in the eastern part of the [[Cape Town]] Metro in the [[Western Cape]] province of [[South Africa]].  Under [[Apartheid]] it was a [[Group Areas Act|group area]] for black people and is still predominantly populated by this community.

